            "actual_output": "The verification lifecycle of a permissible online real money game under Rule 4A involves several key steps and conditions:\n\n1. **Initial Inquiry**: The process begins with the online gaming self-regulatory body conducting an inquiry to determine if the online real money game is permissible. The game must not involve wagering on any outcome and must comply with rules 3 and 4, any applicable laws regarding the age of contractual competence, and the framework set by the self-regulatory body.\n\n2. **Temporary Period**: Upon receiving an application, the self-regulatory body may provisionally declare the game as permissible based on the information provided by the applicant. This provisional status lasts for a period not exceeding three months.\n\n3. **Completion of Inquiry**: Within the three-month period, the self-regulatory body aims to complete its inquiry. After the inquiry, the body will either:\n   - Declare the game as a permissible online real money game, or\n   - Inform the applicant in writing why the game does not meet the requirements.\n\n4. **Publication Requirements**: The self-regulatory body must maintain an updated list on its website and/or mobile application, detailing all verified permissible online real money games. This includes the applicant's details, the dates and validity period of the verification, reasons for verification, and any details regarding suspension or revocation.\n\n5. **Demonstrable Mark**: Verified games and the intermediaries providing access to them must display a visible mark indicating their verification status as permissible, as authorized by the self-regulatory body.\n\n6. **Ongoing Compliance and Revocation**: The self-regulatory body retains the right to suspend or revoke the verification if the game is later found non-compliant with the rules. This decision must be communicated in writing to the applicant, who is also given an opportunity to be heard.\n\n7. **Framework for Verification**: The self-regulatory body must prominently publish a framework for game verification on its website and mobile application, which includes measures to ensure that the game is not against public interest and complies with the outlined standards.\n\nThis lifecycle ensures that online real money games are thoroughly vetted and continuously monitored to maintain compliance with regulatory standards.",
